rComments: Amazing professor! Intelligent, passionate, knowledgeable, caring, and realistic. She is an excellent lecturer and person. Grading TBD, but overall, this class was a positive experience! Only complaint: I wish we had more work throughout the semester instead of just a final paper so people would be inspired to participate more - seminar was fun!
Take her tort law!! She is the most pleasant and approachable prof I've had. She provides powerpoint slides in class. The assigned readings are not long.

Prof Hardcastle is very pleasant, which goes a long way. Many of my classmates felt lost in this class and blamed her for not receiving clear answers, prob b/c there aren't clear answers in Negligence law. Don't hate the player hate the game. She did her best, the admin prob threw this course at her last minute, b/c she was obviously not prepared.

I had this prof for HLST 4000 this year and she was amazing. She is very organized and is very fair when it comes to marking. She opted to mark all of the exams herself (instead of getting a T.A) so that they'll all be marked fairly. She's also very helpful and responds to emails quickly. Overall - an awesome prof who cares about her students!
Excellent prof who really cares about teaching, and knows Health law cold. Would recommend this course to anyone interested in Health law.
